<td valign="top" bgcolor="#FF3300"><p align="left" class="style8">CGVA Mission Statement </p>            </td>
</tr>
<tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<td height="144"><div align="left"><font class='cfont12'>
<p align="justify">The  mission of the Colorado Gay Volleyball Association (CGVA) is to provide access  to volleyball, player education and social activities for the Colorado GLBT  community. </p>
<p>The  CGVA vision creates a balanced environment of athletic, educational and social  activities. This includes recruiting, coaching and mentoring of players through  the organization of its leagues, tournaments, and social events for players.  CGVA is open to players of all skill levels and welcomes all participants.<br />
    <br />
</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td valign="top" bgcolor="#FF3300"><p align="left" class="style8">Current CGVA Offerings </p></td>
</tr>
<tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
  <td height="75"><font class='cfont12'>
    <p>Currently CGVA offers the following events per year:</p>
    <ul>
     <li>League night in the fall running weekly from September through November.</li>
    <li>League night in the spring running from January through April.</li>
    <li>One annual Last Dig in Denver Tournament sanctioned by the <a href="http://www.nagva.org/">North American Gay  Volleyball Association</a> (NAGVA) in March or April.&nbsp; This  tournament is a 6 person pre-formed team format and attracts about 30 teams  each year. </li>
    <li>One annual Volleypalooza Tournament during Denver&rsquo;s Pride-fest  weekend at the end of June.&nbsp; This is a one day outdoor grass tournament  for 4 person pre-formed teams. </li>
    <li>Various volleyball clinics for teams and individuals.</li>
    <li>Various social and fundraising events. </li>
   </ul>
 <br />
  The best way to stay informed about all of our events is to  check out our website OR get on our email list!</p>
